and. like. you know. getting really upset.

227
00:11:21.889 --> 00:11:23.849
I was like. "This isn't fair.
This isn't right."

228
00:11:26.018 --> 00:11:26.852
[music fades]

229
00:11:26.936 --> 00:11:31.774
Me and my sister and Davion
came from a little. uh. tough upbringing.

230
00:11:33.275 --> 00:11:36.028
We were all adopted from foster care.

231
00:11:37.613 --> 00:11:41.951
Davion was always the supporter
and bigger older brother.

232
00:11:42.451 --> 00:11:44.328
He was always there for me.

233
00:11:45.996 --> 00:11:51.419
{\an8}No one should ever have to tell
their kids or their wife

234
00:11:51.919 --> 00:11:54.672
{\an8}that their son or brother.

235
00:11:55.506 --> 00:11:57.717
{\an8}um. had their life taken from them.

236
00:11:58.759 --> 00:12:00.386
It was… It was brutal.

237
00:12:04.849 --> 00:12:08.644
[reporter] <i>The 17-year-old female driver</i>
<i>is listed in a critical condition.</i>

238
00:12:08.728 --> 00:12:12.022
<i>and police are still investigating</i>
<i>the cause of the crash.</i>

239
00:12:12.106 --> 00:12:14.734
[Scott] We really were very much
praying and hoping

240
00:12:14.817 --> 00:12:17.820
that Mackenzie was gonna be okay.

241
00:12:19.196 --> 00:12:23.075
All that we know.
it was a car driving into the building.

242
00:12:23.701 --> 00:12:27.371
But we didn't know why.
We didn't know how.

243
00:12:27.455 --> 00:12:30.124
I wanna know the truth
of what happened to my son.

244
00:12:33.252 --> 00:12:35.629
[dramatic music playing]

245
00:12:41.010 --> 00:12:45.514
[man] I've worked on easily
over a thousand serious felony cases.

246
00:12:46.182 --> 00:12:47.308
{\an8}This is without a doubt

247
00:12:47.391 --> 00:12:49.602
{\an8}the most significant case
I ever worked on.

248
00:12:53.814 --> 00:12:59.195
Strongsville does not have
very much violent crime.

249
00:12:59.278 --> 00:13:00.863
This is a peaceful place.

250
00:13:02.323 --> 00:13:05.493
Their police department
wanted a prosecutor

251
00:13:05.576 --> 00:13:07.703
looking at this case with them.

252
00:13:08.204 --> 00:13:10.498
It's my goal to do everything I can

253
00:13:10.581 --> 00:13:13.209
to provide justice for the families

254
00:13:13.292 --> 00:13:17.922
who have so cruelly had their loved one
taken from them

255
00:13:18.506 --> 00:13:21.008
and try to figure out
what took place out there.

256
00:13:21.509 --> 00:13:22.384
[music stops]

257
00:13:24.470 --> 00:13:30.142
When the police arrived. they see
the interior of the car had exploded.

258
00:13:30.226 --> 00:13:32.603
[tense music playing]

259
00:13:32.686 --> 00:13:35.481
Mackenzie was still wearing her seatbelt.

260
00:13:35.564 --> 00:13:38.567
Her head was beneath the dashboard.

261
00:13:39.819 --> 00:13:43.405
The primary impact
was on Dominic's side of the car.

262
00:13:44.573 --> 00:13:47.201
Dominic was laying in the front seat.

263
00:13:47.284 --> 00:13:50.955
and Davion's laying
stacked on top of Dominic.

264
00:13:52.665 --> 00:13:54.834
First responders did discover

265
00:13:54.917 --> 00:13:57.753
a small amount of marijuana
in Mackenzie's purse.

266
00:13:58.879 --> 00:14:00.339
A digital scale.

267
00:14:00.881 --> 00:14:06.095
Also. eight grams of psilocybin mushrooms
concealed in her clothing.

268
00:14:07.179 --> 00:14:09.348
That was a significant
piece of information.

269
00:14:11.141 --> 00:14:15.980
I'm ticking through the potentials
of what could have caused this crash.

270
00:14:16.772 --> 00:14:18.774
Was it operator error?

271
00:14:19.984 --> 00:14:22.444
Was it substance abuse?

272
00:14:23.654 --> 00:14:26.532
Or could it be a much more serious felony?

273
00:14:28.492 --> 00:14:32.496
We needed to get a full picture
of who Mackenzie Shirilla was.

274
00:14:34.665 --> 00:14:35.749
[uneasy music playing]

275
00:14:35.833 --> 00:14:37.084
What?

276
00:14:39.378 --> 00:14:41.714
-[clicks tongue] Look at that.
-[cat meows]

277
00:14:42.214 --> 00:14:43.090
[Mackenzie gasps]

278
00:14:51.223 --> 00:14:53.559
[woman] Me and Kenzie
met in middle school.

279
00:14:54.977 --> 00:14:58.439
Growing up. we jumped from house to house
'cause we lived so close.

280
00:14:59.690 --> 00:15:01.442
She was like a sister to me.

281
00:15:03.819 --> 00:15:05.154
She's fun.

282
00:15:06.196 --> 00:15:07.197
loving.

283
00:15:09.158 --> 00:15:10.326
an amazing friend.

284
00:15:11.410 --> 00:15:13.370
She would stick up for you.

285
00:15:16.123 --> 00:15:19.877
I remember at school.
I was bullied a little bit.

286
00:15:20.753 --> 00:15:24.798
And Kenzie was like. "Don't talk to her
like that. That's not okay."

287
00:15:25.758 --> 00:15:27.509
She's a very loyal person.

288
00:15:29.219 --> 00:15:33.140
When I heard there was a car crash.
I tried to call Kenzie. like. 50 times.

289
00:15:33.223 --> 00:15:35.225
[tense music playing]

290
00:15:40.731 --> 00:15:42.566
And not getting a response.

291
00:15:43.233 --> 00:15:45.444
And it was immediate panic for me.

292
00:15:45.527 --> 00:15:46.820
[electronic voice] <i>Recording.</i>

293
00:15:51.533 --> 00:15:55.120
[Tim] The day after the crash.
police visited Mackenzie in the hospital

294
00:15:55.204 --> 00:15:59.667
to find out. is she capable
of providing any kind of statement?

295
00:16:05.297 --> 00:16:08.425
[Steve] She had a broken femur
above the knee.

296
00:16:08.509 --> 00:16:12.805
three broken ribs.
a lacerated liver. lacerated kidney.

297
00:16:12.888 --> 00:16:16.433
Th-This bone broke. snapped.
and it detached the tricep.

298
00:16:17.518 --> 00:16:21.021
And both carotid arteries
had damage to 'em from her neck snapping.

299
00:16:23.357 --> 00:16:25.150
She looked like she'd lost a fight.

300
00:16:26.694 --> 00:16:28.654
We just couldn't tell her about Dom

301
00:16:28.737 --> 00:16:30.990
'cause she was just going through so much.

302
00:16:31.532 --> 00:16:33.617
The police started asking her questions.

303
00:16:33.701 --> 00:16:36.245
Then I said. "Wait.
I think we need to get a lawyer."

304
00:16:36.328 --> 00:16:39.707
'Cause you'd said. "Don't say anything
to them without getting a lawyer."

305
00:16:39.790 --> 00:16:42.376
And he goes. "Okay. we won't ask you
any more questions."

306
00:16:42.876 --> 00:16:47.631
[Steve] So then the police attempted
to get access to her cell phone.

307
00:16:48.132 --> 00:16:51.719
That's when he asked me for the passcode.
So of course we gave it.

308
00:16:54.221 --> 00:16:56.765
Go ahead. Go search whatever you want.

309
00:16:59.184 --> 00:17:04.565
[Tim] In this day and age. your cell phone
contains a treasure trove of evidence.

310
00:17:05.107 --> 00:17:08.610
We are looking
for evidence of intoxication.

311
00:17:09.361 --> 00:17:11.447
communication with people.

312
00:17:11.530 --> 00:17:16.118
Social media posts would give some insight
into the events leading up to the crash.

313
00:17:16.201 --> 00:17:17.661
[indistinct chatter]

314
00:17:18.328 --> 00:17:19.329
[music fades]

315
00:17:19.413 --> 00:17:22.791
[Mackenzie] <i>And then I got ready</i>
<i>to hang out with my friends again.</i>

316
00:17:22.875 --> 00:17:24.084
<i>Oh my God. Skims baddie.</i>

317
00:17:24.168 --> 00:17:26.795
<i>She's got the metallic swimsuit. So cute.</i>

318
00:17:26.879 --> 00:17:30.215
<i>We actually went in the lake pretty deep</i>
<i>'cause it was. like. so hot.</i>

319
00:17:30.883 --> 00:17:32.801
[Rosie] In high school
is when I met Kenzie.

320
00:17:32.885 --> 00:17:34.636
[tense music playing]

321
00:17:34.720 --> 00:17:37.389
We started commenting
on each other's Instagrams

322
00:17:37.473 --> 00:17:39.808
before we even
talked to each other in person.

323
00:17:41.018 --> 00:17:44.354
We would. like. comment.
DM back and forth. or Snapchat.

324
00:17:45.898 --> 00:17:46.732
[school bell rings]

325
00:17:46.815 --> 00:17:50.277
She'd make cute little TikTok videos
of her trying on outfits.

326
00:17:52.571 --> 00:17:55.032
She would come to school
with a purse instead of a bag.

327
00:17:55.115 --> 00:17:56.867
which I thought was really cute.

328
00:17:58.118 --> 00:18:00.662
I got along with her well.
I'm like. "You're cute."

329
00:18:00.746 --> 00:18:03.624
She's like. "You're cute."
I'm like. "We get along so well."

330
00:18:08.170 --> 00:18:11.131
When I met her. I had 200K
on TikTok and on YouTube.

331
00:18:11.215 --> 00:18:13.342
and she had. like.
a few thousand followers.

332
00:18:14.927 --> 00:18:16.553
She always wanted to be a model like me.

333
00:18:16.637 --> 00:18:19.473
so me and Kenzie would hang out
and just go do photo shoots.

334
00:18:19.556 --> 00:18:20.474
[music fades]

335
00:18:20.557 --> 00:18:22.142
[Mackenzie] Look at this place.

336
00:18:22.226 --> 00:18:25.771
I'm with Rosie right now.
We gotta do a photo shoot in this bitch.

337
00:18:28.607 --> 00:18:30.567
[Rosie] With Kenzie came Dom.
with Dom came Kenzie.

338
00:18:30.651 --> 00:18:31.735
everywhere they went.

339
00:18:33.445 --> 00:18:34.488
[poignant music playing]

340
00:18:34.571 --> 00:18:38.075
[Faythe] Dom and Kenzie.
they got together in freshman year.

341
00:18:39.910 --> 00:18:41.453
He was three years older.

342
00:18:42.287 --> 00:18:44.331
When we were younger.
it was a bit more like.

343
00:18:44.414 --> 00:18:47.292
"Hey. you're dating an older guy.
This is a lot."

344
00:18:47.376 --> 00:18:50.295
But boyfriends weren't really boyfriends
at the time.

345
00:18:50.379 --> 00:18:54.216
They were very like flings
and "Oh. I wanna flirt and have a crush."

346
00:18:54.299 --> 00:18:57.970
Okay. who's trying to dress up
and go to the Minion movie?

347
00:18:58.053 --> 00:18:59.263
'Cause that looks fun.

348
00:18:59.346 --> 00:19:02.474
We already got two people down.
Yep. me and him.

349
00:19:02.558 --> 00:19:03.517
[both chuckle]

350
00:19:03.600 --> 00:19:05.727
So we're ready to go. Who's coming?

351
00:19:06.228 --> 00:19:08.272
[Faythe] Dom had his own place.

352
00:19:08.814 --> 00:19:11.567
Kenzie moved in after we graduated.

353
00:19:12.484 --> 00:19:15.988
[Steve] Even though she was 17.
we felt she was mature enough to do that.

354
00:19:16.655 --> 00:19:18.240
[Mackenzie] I love you. baby puppy.

355
00:19:18.323 --> 00:19:21.994
They were becoming a little tight couple.
They cooked a lot together.

356
00:19:23.162 --> 00:19:25.330
Always super healthy.
It was always organic.

357
00:19:26.790 --> 00:19:28.458
[Rosie] Dom would buy her clothes.

358
00:19:28.542 --> 00:19:29.543
Oh my God.

359
00:19:29.626 --> 00:19:31.753
That one looks like
the Skims shit but smaller.

360
00:19:31.837 --> 00:19:32.963
I got that as a backup.

361
00:19:33.046 --> 00:19:35.132
-Oh yeah. this looks really cute too.
-[Rosie] Yeah.

362
00:19:35.215 --> 00:19:37.301
-It looks like it's gonna fit me.
-[Rosie] Super cute.

363
00:19:37.384 --> 00:19:39.678
He really loved designer stuff
and just name-brand.

364
00:19:39.761 --> 00:19:40.804
Oh my gosh.

365
00:19:40.888 --> 00:19:42.806
-Dom. no you didn't.
-What?

366
00:19:43.348 --> 00:19:45.976
-[Mackenzie] These are Guccis.
-[Rosie] Okay! Baller.

367
00:19:46.059 --> 00:19:48.687
The boy wasn't hurting for money. okay?

368
00:19:48.770 --> 00:19:52.983
I think that helped Mackenzie a little bit
because Mackenzie likes things.

369
00:19:54.943 --> 00:19:57.112
[Natalie] Kenzie loved Dom
with her whole heart.

370
00:19:57.196 --> 00:19:59.948
I think she was always planning
on getting married to Dom.

371
00:20:00.032 --> 00:20:04.161
-Okay.
-[Rosie] So cute. [chuckles]

372
00:20:07.206 --> 00:20:10.459
[siren wailing]

373
00:20:10.542 --> 00:20:11.376
[music stops]

374
00:20:11.877 --> 00:20:13.253
[electronic voice] <i>Recording.</i>

375
00:20:14.755 --> 00:20:17.174
[Natalie] In the night.
Mackenzie asked. "Where's Dom?"

376
00:20:17.758 --> 00:20:20.594
And I had to tell her…
I had to tell her that it was him.

377
00:20:20.677 --> 00:20:23.222
That he… he didn't… he didn't make it.

378
00:20:24.389 --> 00:20:26.558
So she screamed.
and I said. "I'm so sorry."

379
00:20:26.642 --> 00:20:29.228
-She goes. "No. it's not. It's not him."
-Yeah.

380
00:20:29.311 --> 00:20:30.729
"Please go check. Go check"

381
00:20:30.812 --> 00:20:34.358
And I said. "Mackenzie. it's him.
because if it wasn't him. he'd be here."

382
00:20:35.901 --> 00:20:40.113
That was devastating to hear her.
The sound. It was gut-wrenching.

383
00:20:42.491 --> 00:20:44.243
[Natalie] Right after that.
she was asking.

384
00:20:44.326 --> 00:20:46.203
"What about Davion? Is he okay?"

385
00:20:47.329 --> 00:20:49.414
And I had to say.
"No. he didn't make it either."

386
00:20:49.498 --> 00:20:51.250
And then she was like. "Oh God."

387
00:20:51.333 --> 00:20:53.335
[tense music playing]

388
00:20:55.921 --> 00:20:58.215
[Tim] We really wanted
to talk to Mackenzie

389
00:20:58.298 --> 00:21:01.051
about what took place inside that car.

390
00:21:03.804 --> 00:21:05.013
[Natalie] She remembers waking.

391
00:21:06.640 --> 00:21:08.225
She remembers leaving the house.

392
00:21:09.434 --> 00:21:11.353
Then she remembers turning on the street.

393
00:21:13.438 --> 00:21:14.356
[music fades]

394
00:21:15.774 --> 00:21:17.067
-And then that's it.
-That's it.

395
00:21:17.150 --> 00:21:19.444
She was trying to remember.
Like. she's trying.

396
00:21:19.528 --> 00:21:22.406
I'm like. "Mackenzie. you can't.
It's just not there."

397
00:21:27.286 --> 00:21:28.954
[Mackenzie] <i>I'm not doing okay. like…</i>

398
00:21:29.538 --> 00:21:32.624
<i>It doesn't feel real. I keep saying this.</i>
<i>but it doesn't feel real.</i>

399
00:21:32.708 --> 00:21:34.376
<i>I don't know what the fuck happened.</i>

400
00:21:34.459 --> 00:21:35.335
[voice recorder beeps]

401
00:21:36.628 --> 00:21:38.380
<i>Thank you for being there for me.</i>

402
00:21:38.880 --> 00:21:41.633
<i>It just means a lot.</i>
<i>Like. I don't remember anything.</i>

403
00:21:41.717 --> 00:21:44.136
<i>-Like. this is just the worst.</i>
-[voice recorder beeps]

404
00:21:44.219 --> 00:21:47.222
I can see how someone
could have some amnesia

405
00:21:47.723 --> 00:21:49.433
from the… the impact of the crash.

406
00:21:50.267 --> 00:21:53.437
But the timing just seemed really

407
00:21:54.521 --> 00:21:55.355
perfect.

408
00:21:55.439 --> 00:22:00.527
I don't understand how your amnesia
just lasted the exact right amount of time

409
00:22:01.028 --> 00:22:03.655
to not be able to help the police
with their investigation.

410
00:22:05.157 --> 00:22:06.283
[electronic voice] <i>Recording.</i>

411
00:22:10.037 --> 00:22:11.038
[man] Hey. guys.

412
00:22:11.121 --> 00:22:13.915
[Tim] A couple of days after the crash.

413
00:22:13.999 --> 00:22:17.669
two friends of Davion showed up
at the Strongsville Police Department

414
00:22:19.004 --> 00:22:22.632
and told them
that they could provide some information.

415
00:22:24.259 --> 00:22:26.386
We can literally see where Davion has been

416
00:22:26.470 --> 00:22:28.847
for the past
however long you need to know.

417
00:22:28.930 --> 00:22:29.973
[man] Okay.

418
00:22:30.057 --> 00:22:34.311
[Tim] One of the boys
had an app on his phone called Life360

419
00:22:34.394 --> 00:22:37.522
that was connected to Davion's phone.

420
00:22:37.606 --> 00:22:42.110
where you can monitor
each other's location via GPS.

421
00:22:42.611 --> 00:22:44.571
-[friend 1] I wanna show you.
-[man] Explain it.

422
00:22:44.654 --> 00:22:47.240
[friend 1] This is when they were going
down on Progress Drive.

423
00:22:47.324 --> 00:22:52.162
It shows on this app
Davion was on his phone at 5:35.

424
00:22:52.245 --> 00:22:55.290
-[man] Okay.
-And it says that they crashed at 5:36.

425
00:22:56.541 --> 00:23:00.045
[friend 2] Before that.
they went to a little gathering or party.

426
00:23:00.128 --> 00:23:02.214
-[officer] Graduation party.
-[friend 2] Yeah.

427
00:23:02.714 --> 00:23:04.758
[friend 1] They might have
been on psychedelics.

428
00:23:04.841 --> 00:23:05.759
[officer] Mm-hmm.

429
00:23:05.842 --> 00:23:07.302
[uneasy music playing]

430
00:23:07.386 --> 00:23:09.721
[Tim] This was secondhand information

431
00:23:09.805 --> 00:23:13.058
that there were
drugs of some sort involved

432
00:23:13.141 --> 00:23:15.352
at graduate parties the night before.

433
00:23:16.019 --> 00:23:20.607
Maybe they were on the psychedelics
and she hit the gas…

434
00:23:20.690 --> 00:23:23.652
[officer] All right. guys. thank you.
Appreciate you coming in.

435
00:23:24.486 --> 00:23:28.323
We sent Mackenzie's blood sample
to a lab out of state

436
00:23:28.407 --> 00:23:30.450
because they do not. at our local lab.

437
00:23:30.534 --> 00:23:34.079
test for the psilocybin. for the presence
of that in someone's blood.

438
00:23:39.334 --> 00:23:41.628
But looking at Mackenzie's phone.

439
00:23:41.711 --> 00:23:45.549
there was evidence
of her tripping on mushrooms.

440
00:23:47.759 --> 00:23:50.929
And it seemed to be
almost a daily ritual for her

441
00:23:51.012 --> 00:23:53.056
to smoke marijuana from a bong…

442
00:23:53.140 --> 00:23:54.724
[mellow music playing]

443
00:23:54.808 --> 00:23:57.352
…with her camera propped up
in her clothing closet.

444
00:24:00.313 --> 00:24:03.692
There were some photographs
of her using marijuana

445
00:24:03.775 --> 00:24:07.571
in just the days
or even the day before the crash.

446
00:24:11.908 --> 00:24:16.997
There was multiple videos of her
smoking marijuana and driving that car.

447
00:24:17.080 --> 00:24:17.956
[music fades]

448
00:24:18.039 --> 00:24:20.459
[Steve] I knew. I don't have a problem
with her smoking dope.

449
00:24:20.542 --> 00:24:23.503
I don't have a problem with me smoking it.
with you smoking it.

450
00:24:23.587 --> 00:24:26.882
If you're gonna take a drug.
that's the one I believe you should take.

451
00:24:26.965 --> 00:24:30.427
It's… It's better than alcohol.
It's better than all the other crap.

452
00:24:30.510 --> 00:24:31.678
She's not shooting up.

453
00:24:31.761 --> 00:24:33.763
[mellow music playing]

454
00:24:34.556 --> 00:24:38.310
[Rosie] As typical high schoolers do.
we were kind of. like. the stoners.

455
00:24:41.730 --> 00:24:43.106
It would just be back-to-back fun.

456
00:24:43.190 --> 00:24:45.525
-[Mackenzie] I cannot.
-[Rosie] Okay. State your names.

457
00:24:45.609 --> 00:24:47.444
It's a TikTok.
We don't have that much time.

458
00:24:47.527 --> 00:24:49.738
<i>-I'm Rosie.</i>
<i>-Okay. Hi. my name's Kenzie.</i>

459
00:24:49.821 --> 00:24:52.115
-[Rosie] <i>How are you feeling?</i>
<i>-How am I feeling?</i>

460
00:24:52.616 --> 00:24:53.992
<i>Well. I'm always pimpin'.</i>

461
00:24:54.075 --> 00:24:58.079
<i>-My name's Bubba. I weigh 245 pounds.</i>
-[laughter]

462
00:24:58.163 --> 00:24:59.498
<i>-I'm feeling good.</i>
-[Davion] <i>Damn!</i>

463
00:24:59.581 --> 00:25:01.791
<i>I haven't ate a damn thing</i>
<i>at all today though.</i>

464
00:25:01.875 --> 00:25:03.168
[Rosie] How you guys feeling?

465
00:25:03.251 --> 00:25:07.005
[giggling] I'm geeking. This is crazy!

466
00:25:07.088 --> 00:25:07.964
[music fades]

467
00:25:08.840 --> 00:25:11.176
[Scott] Davion would say to us.
"All the kids are doing it."

468
00:25:11.259 --> 00:25:12.802
"They're all smoking weed."

469
00:25:13.303 --> 00:25:19.476
Me and my wife. Jaime. pushed back
on the narrative that weed is innocent.

470
00:25:19.559 --> 00:25:22.979
"Weed isn't addictive.
Weed's not a gateway drug. Dad."

471
00:25:23.063 --> 00:25:25.315
[indistinct announcer]

472
00:25:25.398 --> 00:25:28.777
In high school.
football was Davion's number-one passion.

473
00:25:28.860 --> 00:25:30.612
[crowd cheering]

474
00:25:31.613 --> 00:25:34.157
-[man on PA] <i>Davion Flanagan.</i>
-[whistle blares]

475
00:25:34.241 --> 00:25:39.079
But four games into his senior season.
he tore his ACL and his UCL.

476
00:25:39.663 --> 00:25:43.959
and he pretty much was told
that his football aspirations

477
00:25:44.042 --> 00:25:47.420
for college and beyond
was over at this point.

478
00:25:47.921 --> 00:25:50.715
I think that's when he started to hang out
with some different people.

479
00:25:51.800 --> 00:25:55.554
different crowds. started experimenting
with illegal substances.

480
00:25:55.637 --> 00:25:57.931
[rock music playing]

481
00:25:58.932 --> 00:26:01.977
[laughter]

482
00:26:06.731 --> 00:26:07.649
[music stops]

483
00:26:07.732 --> 00:26:10.068
He'd come home late. and I would say.

484
00:26:10.151 --> 00:26:12.571
"Show me your friends.
and I'll show you your future. Davion."

485
00:26:13.238 --> 00:26:15.448
[Davion] Oh! Oh shit!

486
00:26:15.532 --> 00:26:17.117
♪ …<i>roof down for the ride… </i>♪

487
00:26:17.200 --> 00:26:18.368
"Please stop."

488
00:26:19.411 --> 00:26:21.746
<i>♪ Do you want to drive? ♪</i>

489
00:26:22.372 --> 00:26:25.875
I think he was just being
a selfish teenager at that point.

490
00:26:25.959 --> 00:26:28.545
like. "Oh. I hate my parents"
type of situation.

491
00:26:28.628 --> 00:26:31.464
where you don't hate them.
you just don't like to follow rules.

492
00:26:33.425 --> 00:26:40.181
You can absolutely drive yourself insane
thinking about the what-ifs.

493
00:26:41.224 --> 00:26:43.226
Could we have done something differently?

494
00:26:43.893 --> 00:26:47.022
If Davion had listened to us.
maybe he never would've been in that car.

495
00:26:47.105 --> 00:26:48.773
[somber music playing]

496
00:26:53.111 --> 00:26:56.406
[Christine] This one over here.
that's my son David.

497
00:26:56.489 --> 00:26:59.200
and he's kissing Dom. which is just…

498
00:26:59.284 --> 00:27:00.619
It melts my heart.

499
00:27:01.119 --> 00:27:04.289
Um. you couldn't buy this picture off me
for a million bucks.

500
00:27:04.372 --> 00:27:05.540
It means the world to me.

501
00:27:07.334 --> 00:27:09.085
He loved his nieces and nephews.

502
00:27:10.795 --> 00:27:14.049
He was there for everything.
every family holiday.

503
00:27:14.549 --> 00:27:16.051
We're a really close family.

504
00:27:16.718 --> 00:27:19.012
-That's part of the worst part.
-[music fades]

505
00:27:19.095 --> 00:27:21.306
He didn't get to see my kids grow up.

506
00:27:23.391 --> 00:27:25.977
You know. you're thinking about your son.

507
00:27:26.061 --> 00:27:28.730
and all of a sudden.
everything leads back to the crash.

508
00:27:29.481 --> 00:27:32.108
In my head. that's just where it goes.
That's where my mind takes me.

509
00:27:32.192 --> 00:27:35.487
What happened? What happened in the car?
What happened? You know?

510
00:27:36.237 --> 00:27:38.239
[tense music playing]

511
00:27:46.289 --> 00:27:48.792
[Tim] We knew
that the night before the crash.

512
00:27:48.875 --> 00:27:53.171
Mackenzie. Dom. and Davion
went to a party.

513
00:28:01.429 --> 00:28:05.308
On the way. there were some text messages
between Mackenzie…

514
00:28:11.523 --> 00:28:13.149
and Rosie Graham.

515
00:28:15.110 --> 00:28:17.779
[Rosie] I was just texting her
to bring over some weed for the night.

516
00:28:19.531 --> 00:28:21.491
We were also talking
about doing the mushrooms.

517
00:28:21.574 --> 00:28:24.411
which is why they brought them
and had them in the car with them.

518
00:28:27.747 --> 00:28:30.834
Rosie would have been
the most likely source of information

519
00:28:30.917 --> 00:28:34.963
on what was going on in Mackenzie's mind
leading up to the crash.

520
00:28:35.046 --> 00:28:36.464
[outgoing call ringing]

521
00:28:36.548 --> 00:28:39.342
[Rosie] The police called
to set up an interview.

522
00:28:39.843 --> 00:28:41.970
and I was like. "I'm not doing it."

523
00:28:42.053 --> 00:28:43.304
[music fades]

524
00:28:43.388 --> 00:28:46.599
People always say
the police will try to say crazy things.

525
00:28:46.683 --> 00:28:48.893
especially if you're alone
and you're a teenager.

526
00:28:48.977 --> 00:28:52.063
It doesn't seem like we're trying to
figure out what happened in the accident.

527
00:28:52.147 --> 00:28:55.734
It seems like we're trying
to track down the next drug dealers.

528
00:28:55.817 --> 00:29:00.363
You have no idea how hard I tried
to get Rosie Graham to talk to me.

529
00:29:00.447 --> 00:29:02.198
to cooperate with me.

530
00:29:02.282 --> 00:29:04.784
But it's good to hear
that she talked to you guys.

531
00:29:05.744 --> 00:29:07.954
I'm fascinated to hear
what she has to say.

532
00:29:08.037 --> 00:29:10.039
[tense music playing]

533
00:29:16.629 --> 00:29:19.090
[Rosie] First of all.
it wasn't a party at all.

534
00:29:19.174 --> 00:29:21.176
Because in my opinion.
and everybody that was there.

535
00:29:21.259 --> 00:29:22.969
we call that a sleepover.

536
00:29:23.052 --> 00:29:26.097
And that was just a friend sleepover
that we would normally do.

537
00:29:28.433 --> 00:29:31.895
I brought. like. a coloring book
and. like. colored pencils.

538
00:29:33.980 --> 00:29:35.982
We were watching YouTube videos.

539
00:29:38.109 --> 00:29:42.113
[Bubba] Me. Dav. and Dom.
we were watching a shark documentary.

540
00:29:42.614 --> 00:29:44.365
Stupid shit on the TV.

541
00:29:46.534 --> 00:29:48.995
A couple of times.
we'd go out and smack the bong.

542
00:29:50.622 --> 00:29:54.083
[Rosie] We were having deep conversations
and just sitting around.

543
00:29:54.167 --> 00:29:56.544
And we were also talking
about doing the mushrooms.

544
00:29:56.628 --> 00:30:00.048
But then by the time they got over.
it was. like. 12:00 a.m..

545
00:30:00.131 --> 00:30:01.925
and we're all like. "It's too late."

546
00:30:02.634 --> 00:30:03.927
[interviewer] So no mushrooms?

547
00:30:04.427 --> 00:30:07.514
Um. yeah. we were all just kind of like.
"It's really late."

548
00:30:07.597 --> 00:30:11.142
and we had. like. weed to smoke.
so we just smoked weed.

549
00:30:12.185 --> 00:30:14.145
Kenzie didn't even smoke that night.

550
00:30:14.229 --> 00:30:17.232
She was on a smoke break
'cause she was coughing up black mucus

551
00:30:17.315 --> 00:30:19.776
or bloody mucus.
something that was really bad.

552
00:30:21.319 --> 00:30:23.655
[Rosie] Kenzie was sleeping
by. like. 3:00 a.m.

553
00:30:25.406 --> 00:30:28.117
All I remember
is Dom just petting her head all night

554
00:30:28.201 --> 00:30:29.994
and cuddling up to her on the couch.

555
00:30:30.078 --> 00:30:32.497
and she was sleeping.
and he was caressing her hair.

556
00:30:32.580 --> 00:30:33.581
[music fades]

557
00:30:34.374 --> 00:30:35.416
[sighs]

558
00:30:36.000 --> 00:30:39.462
All of us all had plans that next day
to go out and do stuff.

559
00:30:39.546 --> 00:30:43.049
There was not one argument.
There was not one moment of tension.

560
00:30:43.132 --> 00:30:47.011
There was not one bad vibe
towards anybody.

561
00:30:47.095 --> 00:30:49.138
[tense music playing]

562
00:30:49.222 --> 00:30:53.184
And then. really early in the morning.
around 5:00. Dom came into the kitchen.

563
00:30:53.268 --> 00:30:55.395
and I was like. "Are you guys leaving?"

564
00:30:57.188 --> 00:31:00.441
[Bubba] And it was right before they left.
me and Davion were talking.

565
00:31:00.525 --> 00:31:03.528
He was supposed to work on my truck
with me the next morning.

566
00:31:03.611 --> 00:31:05.864
And I offered to take him home.

567
00:31:05.947 --> 00:31:07.949
It was set
that he was coming home with me.

568
00:31:08.032 --> 00:31:10.618
And. like. last minute. he goes.

569
00:31:10.702 --> 00:31:13.079
"I wanna shower
and maybe sleep for a little bit."

570
00:31:15.874 --> 00:31:18.501
For some reason. he gave me a hug
and goes. "I love you."

571
00:31:18.585 --> 00:31:19.836
I was like. "Love you too. bro."

572
00:31:19.919 --> 00:31:23.381
Very weird. It was the first time
we said we loved each other for a while.

573
00:31:27.552 --> 00:31:28.595
[music fades]

574
00:31:31.764 --> 00:31:35.268
At that point. when they left the house.
you have this black hole.

575
00:31:35.351 --> 00:31:39.022
The. uh. lack of knowing
what took place inside that car.

576
00:31:43.359 --> 00:31:45.862
But then
Strongsville Police Department called me

577
00:31:45.945 --> 00:31:48.364
about some of the video evidence
that they had uncovered.

578
00:31:50.867 --> 00:31:52.952
[tense music playing]

579
00:31:59.584 --> 00:32:01.336
I'm Trooper Elliot Rawson.

580
00:32:02.462 --> 00:32:06.132
I serve as a crash-reconstruction trooper
with the Ohio State Highway Patrol.

581
00:32:11.596 --> 00:32:13.556
We had obtained surveillance camera video

582
00:32:13.640 --> 00:32:15.892
of the final moments
leading up to the event.

583
00:32:19.103 --> 00:32:21.814
{\an8}All right. so this is
the first camera vantage point. um.

584
00:32:21.898 --> 00:32:25.026
{\an8}from the intersection
of Progress Road at Pearl Road.

585
00:32:26.903 --> 00:32:29.739
Here. we can see
the Toyota traveling southbound.

586
00:32:30.281 --> 00:32:32.533
and it begins to make a right turn.

587
00:32:34.661 --> 00:32:37.413
[mouse clicking]

588
00:32:37.497 --> 00:32:40.458
As it traveled west
for nearly a half mile…

589
00:32:42.543 --> 00:32:44.212
there was a slight bend

590
00:32:44.295 --> 00:32:46.714
where the second piece
of video evidence comes from.

591
00:32:47.215 --> 00:32:50.426
The camera was located
on the southern face of this building.

592
00:32:50.510 --> 00:32:51.719
pointing southwest.

593
00:32:58.810 --> 00:33:00.687
Based on my calculations.

594
00:33:00.770 --> 00:33:03.731
the Toyota averaged
approximately 97.8 miles per hour

595
00:33:03.815 --> 00:33:06.442
through this stretch right here.

596
00:33:06.943 --> 00:33:10.989
That's beyond unsafe speed
for the roadway and conditions.

597
00:33:15.535 --> 00:33:18.496
At this point.
the Toyota enters the intersection

598
00:33:18.579 --> 00:33:21.708
where it struck the corner
of the commercial building.

599
00:33:23.793 --> 00:33:24.752
[music fades]

600
00:33:27.171 --> 00:33:29.173
[engine roars]

601
00:33:29.799 --> 00:33:31.259
[tires screeching]

602
00:33:31.342 --> 00:33:34.804
[car crashing]

603
00:33:40.018 --> 00:33:41.644
My first thoughts…

604
00:33:42.395 --> 00:33:43.980
It was just chilling.

605
00:33:46.482 --> 00:33:52.238
If… If anybody was awake and alert
inside that car.

606
00:33:53.197 --> 00:33:56.576
what a horrific last few seconds

607
00:33:57.326 --> 00:33:58.995
they endured.

608
00:33:59.078 --> 00:34:01.998
It was hard to comprehend that someone

609
00:34:02.540 --> 00:34:05.585
could just drive into a wall
at that kind of speed.

610
00:34:07.795 --> 00:34:13.051
I looked back at the video of Mackenzie
turning from Pearl Road onto Progress.

611
00:34:15.178 --> 00:34:16.429
It just didn't add up.

612
00:34:18.264 --> 00:34:21.100
It was not someone
who's driving with the music loud.

613
00:34:21.184 --> 00:34:22.935
throwing beer cans out of the car.

614
00:34:23.019 --> 00:34:25.730
This turning was controlled
and deliberate.

615
00:34:25.813 --> 00:34:27.815
[ominous music playing]

616
00:34:31.611 --> 00:34:34.363
And then when we get
the blood toxicology back.

617
00:34:35.490 --> 00:34:38.076
the blood test indicated no alcohol.

618
00:34:39.619 --> 00:34:44.123
They did find THC. the active chemical
contained in marijuana.

619
00:34:47.210 --> 00:34:51.380
But this was not someone
who was unfamiliar with driving

620
00:34:51.464 --> 00:34:53.466
under the effects of marijuana.

621
00:34:57.637 --> 00:35:00.014
But the most significant piece of evidence

622
00:35:00.807 --> 00:35:02.809
was that she has no psilocybin
in her system.

623
00:35:05.061 --> 00:35:08.189
So this was not
some sort of party gone wrong.

624
00:35:09.524 --> 00:35:13.486
She wasn't high on psilocybin
when she crashed.

625
00:35:14.612 --> 00:35:16.239
That ended that rabbit hole.

626
00:35:16.322 --> 00:35:17.156
[music fades]

627
00:35:17.240 --> 00:35:19.117
Now we know this isn't impaired driving.

628
00:35:21.035 --> 00:35:23.204
What else would help explain this crash?

629
00:35:25.248 --> 00:35:27.291
Was something tampered with?

630
00:35:28.042 --> 00:35:30.545
Or did the car malfunction in some way?

631
00:35:31.045 --> 00:35:34.590
The police did observe
a fuzzy Prada slipper

632
00:35:34.674 --> 00:35:38.553
that appeared to be stuck
to the floorboard

633
00:35:38.636 --> 00:35:41.264
next to the accelerator pedal.

634
00:35:41.347 --> 00:35:42.640
[somber music playing]

635
00:35:42.723 --> 00:35:44.725
Had that contributed to the crash?

636
00:35:46.727 --> 00:35:50.940
We needed to retain
a forensic auto investigator

637
00:35:51.023 --> 00:35:53.860
to do a complete analysis of that car.

638
00:35:57.196 --> 00:35:59.198
[tense music playing]

639
00:36:01.617 --> 00:36:04.620
[reporter 1] <i>This Strongsville community</i>
<i>is devastated.</i>

640
00:36:04.704 --> 00:36:06.998
<i>The cause of that crash is unclear.</i>

641
00:36:07.081 --> 00:36:09.876
[reporter 2] <i>Police say</i>
<i>speed was one of the factors.</i>

642
00:36:09.959 --> 00:36:12.587
[Scott] The police would contact us
at least once a week

643
00:36:12.670 --> 00:36:14.213
and give us an update.

644
00:36:14.755 --> 00:36:16.591
But they held a lot back as well

645
00:36:17.091 --> 00:36:19.927
because they needed
to keep their cards close to their vest.

646
00:36:20.011 --> 00:36:20.887
[music stops]

647
00:36:21.679 --> 00:36:27.059
And then I saw an Instagram post
that was sent to Mackenzie from a brand

648
00:36:27.143 --> 00:36:29.312
a day or two after the crash.

649
00:36:29.395 --> 00:36:31.689
[tense music playing]

650
00:36:32.773 --> 00:36:37.361
"We love this look. Can we use this post
on our website and emails?"

651
00:36:37.904 --> 00:36:40.114
It's answered by Mackenzie's mother.

652
00:36:42.033 --> 00:36:43.534
Natalie Shirilla.

653
00:36:43.618 --> 00:36:45.995
"Thank you for this amazing opportunity."

654
00:36:46.078 --> 00:36:48.289
"She would love if you would use that."

655
00:36:48.372 --> 00:36:51.792
"She's actually been trying
to contact you guys for PR email."

656
00:36:52.293 --> 00:36:53.878
"It was a tragic accident."

657
00:36:53.961 --> 00:36:58.507
"This is just as painful for her
as it is for everybody else."

658
00:36:59.175 --> 00:37:02.428
"Or maybe even a little more painful."

659
00:37:05.139 --> 00:37:06.057
[music fades]

660
00:37:06.140 --> 00:37:08.643
Then Mackenzie responds.

661
00:37:09.268 --> 00:37:11.520
"Thank you for the comment.
I would love to work with you."

662
00:37:11.604 --> 00:37:15.191
"I've been emailing you guys a lot.
Such a great opportunity. Thank you."

663
00:37:16.943 --> 00:37:19.070
The only term that comes to mind
is tone-deaf.

664
00:37:19.153 --> 00:37:24.617
Like. she just doesn't get
how much anguish she's caused.

665
00:37:25.618 --> 00:37:26.953
No one in their right mind

666
00:37:27.036 --> 00:37:29.956
would post about being thrilled
about this opportunity

667
00:37:30.039 --> 00:37:34.126
after they just killed two people
in a horrific accident.

668
00:37:34.627 --> 00:37:38.047
It just felt off.

669
00:37:39.882 --> 00:37:40.800
[cell phone beeps]

670
00:37:41.884 --> 00:37:44.553
[Davyne] I got a DM
on Instagram from Mackenzie.

671
00:37:45.054 --> 00:37:47.723
She said. basically. "I'm sorry."

672
00:37:47.807 --> 00:37:52.228
"Davion was like a brother to me.
It was all an accident. I didn't mean to."

673
00:37:52.311 --> 00:37:55.314
She wanted to get her peace out of it.

674
00:37:55.815 --> 00:37:58.359
At the end of the day.
I didn't feel like I needed to respond

675
00:37:58.442 --> 00:38:00.027
to someone who killed my brother.

676
00:38:00.111 --> 00:38:01.821
[tense music playing]

677
00:38:04.031 --> 00:38:06.951
Me and Mackenzie.
we went to the same school.

678
00:38:08.494 --> 00:38:10.955
but we were in a different year.

679
00:38:11.455 --> 00:38:15.251
Dude. why is the lighting in here
fucking terrible? Like. what the fuck?

680
00:38:16.419 --> 00:38:19.422
[Davyne] I already had.
like. my opinion on her.

681
00:38:19.505 --> 00:38:22.300
and I'd expressed that
to Davion privately.

682
00:38:22.383 --> 00:38:23.551
[Mackenzie] <i>I'm not even cool.</i>

683
00:38:23.634 --> 00:38:27.013
<i>I'm just one of those girls</i>
<i>that can do a lot of drugs and not die.</i>

684
00:38:27.638 --> 00:38:29.807
She gave off this persona and this act

685
00:38:29.890 --> 00:38:32.643
of being. like. high up
and better than everyone else.

686
00:38:32.727 --> 00:38:35.646
I don't like when people
talk about the world.

687
00:38:35.730 --> 00:38:38.607
and they're like. "We're all gonna be dead
in 60 years anyways."

688
00:38:38.691 --> 00:38:41.736
Please go fucking kill yourself.
Yep. I said it. Go die. bitch.

689
00:38:45.197 --> 00:38:47.616
[Davyne] I heard
people would steer away from her

690
00:38:47.700 --> 00:38:49.827
because she got very aggressive

691
00:38:49.910 --> 00:38:52.580
and could bully people
and talk bad about people.

692
00:38:54.000 --> 00:39:00.074
Press play. Subtitles appear.
200+ languages. One app:  tryray.app

693
00:39:02.882 --> 00:39:05.968
The school records showed
one incident after the next

694
00:39:06.052 --> 00:39:09.930
of disrespect to teachers
and fellow students.

695
00:39:13.976 --> 00:39:16.020
