and I don't wanna be around her anymore.
I'm done."

930
00:53:21.406 --> 00:53:23.158
So I get on the highway.

931
00:53:24.701 --> 00:53:26.828
And I call him. I say. "Where are you at?"

932
00:53:26.912 --> 00:53:30.707
She was like. "I'll crash this car."
I'm like. "Dude. what do you mean?"

933
00:53:31.208 --> 00:53:34.002
[officer] Can you clarify again
what you heard her say over the phone?

934
00:53:34.085 --> 00:53:36.630
-[Chris] She said she'll crash this car.
-[officer] You heard her?

935
00:53:36.713 --> 00:53:37.839
-[Chris] Yes.
-[officer] Okay.

936
00:53:38.423 --> 00:53:42.052
So we had a witness
who had heard her say those words.

937
00:53:42.135 --> 00:53:44.721
Mackenzie had threatened
to crash a car with Dominic

938
00:53:44.804 --> 00:53:46.181
two weeks before she did.

939
00:53:46.264 --> 00:53:49.935
In criminal cases.
we call that prior calculation.

940
00:53:50.018 --> 00:53:52.020
[tense music playing]

941
00:54:01.321 --> 00:54:03.949
[Scott] For three months. we had heard.

942
00:54:04.032 --> 00:54:06.493
"We have evidence.
We have evidence. We have evidence."

943
00:54:06.576 --> 00:54:08.495
"So when are you gonna arrest her?"

944
00:54:08.578 --> 00:54:10.705
"If you have evidence.
when is this gonna take place?"

945
00:54:10.789 --> 00:54:14.417
"When is the wheels of justice
finally gonna start to turn?"

946
00:54:16.586 --> 00:54:20.757
[Tim] The evidence that we had
in this case was compelling.

947
00:54:22.759 --> 00:54:24.177
100% gas pedal.

948
00:54:24.261 --> 00:54:28.932
No attempt at using the brake.
The car didn't fail.

949
00:54:29.599 --> 00:54:33.353
She wasn't on some kind
of mind-altering substance.

950
00:54:33.937 --> 00:54:38.483
Mackenzie and Dominic had an incredibly
toxic and failing relationship.

951
00:54:38.566 --> 00:54:39.484
[music stops]

952
00:54:39.567 --> 00:54:44.322
We were left
with no reasonable alternative

953
00:54:44.406 --> 00:54:47.909
but that she did it on purpose. because
that's what all the evidence indicated.

954
00:54:48.952 --> 00:54:50.954
[tense music playing]

955
00:54:58.169 --> 00:55:00.672
[Natalie] Mackenzie was
going to physical therapy.

956
00:55:01.548 --> 00:55:06.636
After we left that appointment.
I had gotten pulled over.

957
00:55:16.563 --> 00:55:18.023
[officer 1] I'll go back to her.

958
00:55:20.191 --> 00:55:21.276
Hi. Mackenzie.

959
00:55:21.985 --> 00:55:23.403
[Mackenzie] Don't touch my phone!

960
00:55:23.486 --> 00:55:26.114
[officer 2] You're under arrest.
We have a warrant for your arrest.

961
00:55:26.197 --> 00:55:29.951
[Mackenzie] Why? Wait. we have a lawyer.
I have to call my lawyer.

962
00:55:32.912 --> 00:55:35.123
I don't know
why they needed nine or ten cars

963
00:55:35.206 --> 00:55:37.959
to roll up on an 18. 17-year-old girl.

964
00:55:38.043 --> 00:55:41.171
Prosecution needed a show.
and they wanted to put on a pageant.

965
00:55:41.254 --> 00:55:43.882
-Where is she?
-[officer 3] Right back there. pal.

966
00:55:47.469 --> 00:55:49.888
[officer 4] Hi. Mackenzie.
Step out for me.

967
00:55:51.848 --> 00:55:52.849
I'm Detective Hazou.

968
00:55:52.932 --> 00:55:55.143
I'm the one
who's been investigating the crash.

969
00:55:55.226 --> 00:55:57.771
You're under arrest
for aggravated murder times two.

970
00:55:59.522 --> 00:56:02.359
-Murder? What? What?!
-I was…

971
00:56:02.442 --> 00:56:04.110
Yeah. we were just… It was shock.

972
00:56:04.194 --> 00:56:05.028
[music stops]

973
00:56:07.655 --> 00:56:09.240
[reporter] <i>Breaking news alert.</i>

974
00:56:09.324 --> 00:56:13.870
<i>An arrest in a deadly car crash involving</i>
<i>two Strongsville High School grads.</i>

975
00:56:13.953 --> 00:56:16.706
<i>We've learned now</i>
<i>18-year-old Mackenzie Shirilla</i>

976
00:56:16.790 --> 00:56:19.959
{\an8}<i>has been charged with two counts</i>
<i>of aggravated murder.</i>

977
00:56:20.043 --> 00:56:21.336
{\an8}[dramatic music playing]

978
00:56:22.921 --> 00:56:25.423
{\an8}Taking that news in.
you're stunned for a while.

979
00:56:25.507 --> 00:56:27.300
You can't say or do anything.

980
00:56:27.384 --> 00:56:29.636
-I was shocked when she was arrested.
-Yeah.

981
00:56:29.719 --> 00:56:32.722
I was like. "What? W… why?
Was it the drugs?"

982
00:56:32.806 --> 00:56:35.683
No. they think she actually murdered him.

983
00:56:35.767 --> 00:56:39.187
'Cause all along.
we wanted it to be an accident.

984
00:56:39.687 --> 00:56:42.273
We didn't want someone
to intentionally murder our son.

985
00:56:46.069 --> 00:56:48.238
The day she got arrested.
everyone was chanting.

986
00:56:48.321 --> 00:56:51.116
Everyone was like.
"Oh. she's gone! She's arrested."

987
00:56:54.160 --> 00:56:56.371
I didn't think
she would get arrested at all for this.

988
00:56:56.454 --> 00:56:58.957
That's the last thing I'm thinking about.

989
00:56:59.040 --> 00:57:02.919
I'm thinking. "Our friends are dead.
How are we gonna recover from this?"

990
00:57:08.675 --> 00:57:11.553
You guys are acting like
this is Jeffrey Dahmer or someone.

991
00:57:11.636 --> 00:57:15.306
Someone that's out here.
like. calculating these murders

992
00:57:15.390 --> 00:57:17.934
and calculating these things.
No. that's not who she was.

993
00:57:18.518 --> 00:57:21.813
<i>Could you be careful taking this one off</i>
<i>so it doesn't break the bracelet?</i>

994
00:57:21.896 --> 00:57:23.523
-[officer] <i>You got it.</i>
<i>-Thank you.</i>

995
00:57:23.606 --> 00:57:26.317
I've seen so many people be like.
"This dramatic girl.

996
00:57:26.401 --> 00:57:29.195
she's going to prison
worrying about her bracelets."

997
00:57:29.279 --> 00:57:30.572
[officer] I don't wanna hurt you.

998
00:57:33.616 --> 00:57:36.161
[Rosie] But all of her bracelets
are. like. Dom bracelets.

999
00:57:36.244 --> 00:57:39.205
She just didn't wanna break
the things that Dom had given her.

1000
00:57:39.289 --> 00:57:42.208
It's. like. the only…
The last thing that she has. She…

1001
00:57:42.959 --> 00:57:44.419
She was so sad about it all.

1002
00:57:45.420 --> 00:57:47.755
[officer] Here you go.
Watch your head going in.

1003
00:57:48.256 --> 00:57:49.674
[Mackenzie grunts. sniffles]

1004
00:57:53.178 --> 00:57:55.180
[tense music playing]

1005
00:58:21.331 --> 00:58:22.332
[officer 1] This way.

1006
00:58:23.249 --> 00:58:25.251
Okay. I'm gonna take your handcuffs off.

1007
00:58:25.335 --> 00:58:27.795
-I need all the jewelry to come off. okay?
-Okay.

1008
00:58:28.296 --> 00:58:29.547
I can't wear any of it?

1009
00:58:29.631 --> 00:58:32.425
No. I need you to take it off
while you're in the jail right now.

1010
00:58:34.552 --> 00:58:37.055
[officer 1] As soon as we're done.
you'll be able to make a call.

1011
00:58:37.138 --> 00:58:39.474
[officer 2] We have to wait
for the detective to come back.

1012
00:58:39.557 --> 00:58:41.017
Just have a seat for us.

1013
00:59:03.289 --> 00:59:04.123
[music fades]

1014
00:59:04.207 --> 00:59:08.753
[interviewer] So could you tell me why you
want to give this interview. Mackenzie?

1015
00:59:10.713 --> 00:59:15.510
I've never spoke before.
and I never told my side of the story.

1016
00:59:15.593 --> 00:59:20.014
I understand there's many different sides
to the story and different perspectives.

1017
00:59:20.098 --> 00:59:22.976
but I just wanna say my truth. and

1018
00:59:23.935 --> 00:59:28.189
I just know myself.
and I know I'm not… a monster.

1019
00:59:29.065 --> 00:59:30.858
[uneasy music playing]

1020
00:59:33.111 --> 00:59:34.237
[laughter echoes]

1021
00:59:34.320 --> 00:59:35.154
[music fades]

1022
00:59:35.238 --> 00:59:37.574
We were just two kids
messing with each other.

1023
00:59:37.657 --> 00:59:42.078
And then. as the years went on
and we stayed together and grew closer.

1024
00:59:42.579 --> 00:59:44.831
we would have probably
been married by now.

1025
00:59:45.790 --> 00:59:47.625
[uneasy music playing]

1026
00:59:47.709 --> 00:59:49.877
He was just so protective
and loving over me.

1027
00:59:49.961 --> 00:59:53.506
I wanted to just heal him.
and he wanted to heal me.

1028
00:59:54.340 --> 00:59:57.260
We were partners.
We just took care of each other.

1029
00:59:58.094 --> 01:00:02.932
I mean. we argued. we got back together.
We broke up. we got back together.

1030
01:00:03.016 --> 01:00:06.227
It was… It was rocky. but it was good.

1031
01:00:06.311 --> 01:00:07.437
It was just…

1032
01:00:07.937 --> 01:00:09.606
We were in love. Young love.

1033
01:00:10.565 --> 01:00:14.611
[interviewer] Did you ever feel.
in your arguments with Dom.

1034
01:00:14.694 --> 01:00:17.447
rage that you couldn't control?

1035
01:00:18.364 --> 01:00:19.782
No. it was never like that.

1036
01:00:19.866 --> 01:00:21.784
It was always just like more. I was…

1037
01:00:21.868 --> 01:00:23.286
When we'd argue. I'd get sad

1038
01:00:23.369 --> 01:00:26.414
because he didn't really have
good communication skills.

1039
01:00:26.497 --> 01:00:31.044
and we would be cool later that day
or a couple of hours later.

1040
01:00:31.127 --> 01:00:34.422
and we would be watching movies
on the couch. eating popcorn.

1041
01:00:38.551 --> 01:00:41.137
Davion. he was more of Dom's friend.

1042
01:00:41.638 --> 01:00:45.725
That summer. he came to live with me
and Dom for a week or two.

1043
01:00:45.808 --> 01:00:49.395
and during those couple of weeks.
I was growing really close to Davion.

1044
01:00:49.479 --> 01:00:53.066
He was just full of life.
He was a good person.

1045
01:00:54.108 --> 01:00:56.110
[tense music playing]

1046
01:00:58.821 --> 01:01:03.368
[interviewer] What do you remember
from the morning of July 31st?

1047
01:01:06.120 --> 01:01:07.747
[Mackenzie] It was 5:00 in the morning.

1048
01:01:07.830 --> 01:01:13.127
and we decided to head back
to Dom's house. and…

1049
01:01:13.211 --> 01:01:14.587
[music stops]

1050
01:01:14.671 --> 01:01:16.506
I remember turning on the street.

1051
01:01:16.589 --> 01:01:21.761
and then I'm waking up in the hospital
the next day. and I don't…

1052
01:01:23.429 --> 01:01:25.390
Then my whole life is shattered.

1053
01:01:26.516 --> 01:01:30.395
[interviewer] People have said that it's
convenient that that's all you remember.

1054
01:01:30.478 --> 01:01:31.938
What would you say to that?

1055
01:01:32.939 --> 01:01:36.067
[interviewer] The whole morning
is just. like. nothing. and I…

1056
01:01:36.150 --> 01:01:37.819
It sounds crazy. but I…

1057
01:01:38.319 --> 01:01:42.448
Like. I can't… I'm not gonna. like. lie
just because people wanna hear a story.

1058
01:01:42.532 --> 01:01:45.993
I have no recollection of that morning.

1059
01:01:47.620 --> 01:01:51.040
I'm not saying I'm… innocent.

1060
01:01:51.124 --> 01:01:53.876
I was a driver of a tragedy.

1061
01:01:54.377 --> 01:01:55.795
But I'm not a murderer.

1062
01:01:56.295 --> 01:01:58.297
[dramatic classical music playing]

1063
01:02:12.270 --> 01:02:14.605
[reporter 1] <i>The trial</i>
<i>for a Strongsville teen charged</i>

1064
01:02:14.689 --> 01:02:15.982
<i>with murder in a deadly crash</i>

1065
01:02:16.065 --> 01:02:17.650
<i>is going on today.</i>

1066
01:02:17.734 --> 01:02:22.113
The accident happened just days
before Mackenzie Shirilla's 18th birthday.

1067
01:02:22.196 --> 01:02:25.032
[reporter 2] <i>Shirilla is now facing</i>
<i>murder. felonious assault.</i>

1068
01:02:25.116 --> 01:02:27.785
<i>and aggravated vehicular homicide charges.</i>

1069
01:02:28.286 --> 01:02:30.079
Good luck proving it. There's no…

1070
01:02:30.163 --> 01:02:31.330
-What proof?
-Yeah.

1071
01:02:31.414 --> 01:02:34.083
What proof… What proof do they have
to any of this?

1072
01:02:35.626 --> 01:02:38.755
[Tim] In Ohio. a defendant chooses

1073
01:02:38.838 --> 01:02:41.883
whether to have a jury trial
or a bench trial.

1074
01:02:41.966 --> 01:02:45.261
A bench trial is tried just to the judge.

1075
01:02:46.012 --> 01:02:49.348
Mackenzie Shirilla
opted for a bench trial.

1076
01:02:50.641 --> 01:02:55.897
[Scott] We were gonna get our day in court
but we absolutely were in fear and terror

1077
01:02:55.980 --> 01:02:58.524
that we would not get earthly justice
for our son.

1078
01:02:58.608 --> 01:03:00.902
[tense music playing]

1079
01:03:00.985 --> 01:03:04.447
We went to the first hearing
and sat with their family.

1080
01:03:04.947 --> 01:03:05.907
Yep.

1081
01:03:06.449 --> 01:03:08.034
[interviewer] Sat with the Shirillas?

1082
01:03:08.117 --> 01:03:09.619
Mm-hmm.

1083
01:03:11.412 --> 01:03:15.374
We still thought she had been drinking
or there were drugs involved.

1084
01:03:16.042 --> 01:03:19.378
You know. they were kids.
Accidents happen all the time like that.

1085
01:03:19.462 --> 01:03:21.214
You never in a million years think

1086
01:03:22.215 --> 01:03:24.383
this girl killed your brother.

1087
01:03:24.967 --> 01:03:26.135
You just don't think that way.

1088
01:03:29.806 --> 01:03:35.144
All of the records will show.
from when the police first responded.

1089
01:03:35.228 --> 01:03:39.273
she had no recollection of the events.

1090
01:03:39.357 --> 01:03:43.528
and that is consistent
with what happens many times in accidents.

1091
01:03:44.487 --> 01:03:50.618
My attorney was very reassuring
of there being no evidence

1092
01:03:50.701 --> 01:03:54.622
and that anyone can see
that there was no intent.

1093
01:03:54.705 --> 01:04:00.461
How can you come to any conclusion
other than. if anything. she's reckless?

1094
01:04:02.046 --> 01:04:05.299
Your Honor. at issue
in this case. primarily.

1095
01:04:05.383 --> 01:04:08.970
is the defendant's state of mind
at the time of the fatal crash.

1096
01:04:09.554 --> 01:04:11.639
The evidence in this case is clear.

1097
01:04:12.223 --> 01:04:14.141
She drove the car into the wall.

1098
01:04:14.225 --> 01:04:17.019
She made up her mind.
and she never went back.

1099
01:04:17.103 --> 01:04:19.021
[eerie music playing]

1100
01:04:19.105 --> 01:04:21.065
[Scott] The prosecutor would alert us

1101
01:04:21.148 --> 01:04:23.192
to what they were gonna show
in the courtroom.

1102
01:04:23.693 --> 01:04:27.071
This is two-tenths of a mile
from the ultimate crash site.

1103
01:04:27.154 --> 01:04:29.699
[Scott] We saw the video
for the first time.

1104
01:04:31.492 --> 01:04:33.452
[Tim] You will hear the Camry coming

1105
01:04:33.536 --> 01:04:36.497
before you see
the last few seconds before impact.

1106
01:04:37.123 --> 01:04:39.250
-Oh my gosh.
-It was torture.

1107
01:04:39.333 --> 01:04:41.752
And you kept saying
it was like a bomb went off.

1108
01:04:41.836 --> 01:04:44.255
-Yeah. it was like a torpedo.
-[Christine] A missile.

1109
01:04:45.172 --> 01:04:47.341
[car engine roars]

1110
01:04:47.425 --> 01:04:50.595
[car crashing]

1111
01:04:51.554 --> 01:04:52.930
-Brutal.
-[Christine] Mm-hmm.

1112
01:04:53.014 --> 01:04:54.015
Brutal.

1113
01:04:54.724 --> 01:04:57.184
That's embedded.
You never get rid of that.

1114
01:04:58.811 --> 01:05:03.190
[Scott] There was a pause.
and my wife. Jaime.

1115
01:05:03.858 --> 01:05:05.693
went into the bathroom and threw up.

1116
01:05:06.569 --> 01:05:12.116
100% acceleration
through the entire final five seconds.

1117
01:05:12.199 --> 01:05:14.201
[somber music playing]

1118
01:05:14.869 --> 01:05:19.081
No service brake was deployed
during that final five seconds.

1119
01:05:19.582 --> 01:05:22.293
-What other explanation do you have?
-[Christine] 100 miles an hour.

1120
01:05:22.376 --> 01:05:25.254
100% acceleration. Never hit a brake.

1121
01:05:25.338 --> 01:05:28.341
It was a big slap in the face.
thinking we're there for her

1122
01:05:28.424 --> 01:05:32.303
'cause we feel bad for her too.
and then it's all a lie.

1123
01:05:35.765 --> 01:05:38.100
[reporter] <i>It's day two</i>
<i>in the trial of the Strongsville teen</i>

1124
01:05:38.184 --> 01:05:40.895
<i>charged with murder in a deadly crash.</i>

1125
01:05:40.978 --> 01:05:42.063
[somber music continues]

1126
01:05:42.146 --> 01:05:44.357
When I first got this case

1127
01:05:45.358 --> 01:05:47.318
and saw that the charge was murder.

1128
01:05:47.902 --> 01:05:52.323
I thought to myself.
"Boy. if she's driving the car.

1129
01:05:52.406 --> 01:05:56.327
and it was her purpose
to kill these people.

1130
01:05:56.410 --> 01:05:58.621
she must have wanted to kill herself too."

1131
01:06:01.749 --> 01:06:04.710
In fact. we know
that she was not suicidal.

1132
01:06:05.628 --> 01:06:09.173
I would never. ever see her
purposely wanting to hurt herself.

1133
01:06:09.256 --> 01:06:11.550
Say that is.
and she's so sad. like mentally.

1134
01:06:11.634 --> 01:06:13.719
I… I don't think that's the way to do it.

1135
01:06:14.637 --> 01:06:16.764
[Faythe] Kenzie loves herself a lot.

1136
01:06:16.847 --> 01:06:19.976
She wouldn't even have a McChicken
with me at McDonald's

1137
01:06:20.059 --> 01:06:22.144
because she cared so much
about her own health.

1138
01:06:22.228 --> 01:06:24.897
I don't feel like somebody like that.

1139
01:06:24.981 --> 01:06:28.109
who's caring so much about their body
and so much about

1140
01:06:29.110 --> 01:06:31.195
themselves and how they're doing.

1141
01:06:31.278 --> 01:06:32.863
would be suicidal.

1142
01:06:33.948 --> 01:06:35.324
[Rosie] Her birthday was coming up.

1143
01:06:35.408 --> 01:06:39.203
She had an expensive designer outfit
ready to wear.

1144
01:06:40.538 --> 01:06:43.165
She had presents ready.
wrapped up from Dom.

1145
01:06:43.249 --> 01:06:44.959
that she still has never opened.

1146
01:06:45.751 --> 01:06:48.921
Nothing makes sense. It really doesn't.

1147
01:06:49.588 --> 01:06:53.676
[Tim] Mr. McDonnell brought up the issue
of her trying to kill herself.

1148
01:06:53.759 --> 01:06:55.594
How could anybody do that?

1149
01:06:55.678 --> 01:07:00.391
Everybody that's heard this evidence
can't figure out

1150
01:07:00.474 --> 01:07:02.685
how could anybody do that.

1151
01:07:02.768 --> 01:07:05.813
We don't have to prove
that she was suicidal.

1152
01:07:05.896 --> 01:07:08.107
but she put that car into the wall.

1153
01:07:08.190 --> 01:07:10.484
and the results were as foreseeable

1154
01:07:10.568 --> 01:07:13.446
as if she drove that car
off of the Grand Canyon.

1155
01:07:14.196 --> 01:07:16.157
[James] Is it just kids being kids?

1156
01:07:16.240 --> 01:07:18.492
Is it Dominic grabbing the steering wheel?

1157
01:07:19.285 --> 01:07:20.995
